Tanzania`s CRDB Bank Emerged The Overall Winner In The Just Concluded 2019 Financial Reporting Awards. According To Ibrahim Haji The Banks Representative At The Event, Teamwork And Good Governance Were The Success Factor For The Bank The Awards Meant To Recognise Institutions Which Best Discloses Financial Information To The Various Stakeholders About The Financial Performance And Financial Position Of The Organization, Also Saw Kenya`s NIC Bank And Stanbic Bank Uganda Holding Limited Outdo The Other Banks In The Country To Be Awarded As The Best Banks In Their Respective Nations. The Award Brought Together over 600 Participants from Both the Public and Private Sector .The Public Sector Dominated The Entries As It Accounted For 87%Percent Of The Entries With A Tally Of 602 Out Of The Total 693